## ADDITIONAL TERMS & CONDITIONS

### Purpose
This portfolio is intended to demonstrate cybersecurity expertise, full-stack
development capabilities, and best practices in modern web development. It
serves as a reference implementation and educational resource.

### Use Cases
✅ Educational purposes and learning from code examples
✅ Reference implementation for portfolio best practices
✅ Forking and customizing for your own portfolio project
✅ Integration into larger projects (subject to license compliance)
✅ Security research and code review

❌ Commercial use without attribution
❌ Removal of copyright notices or license terms
❌ Claiming the portfolio as your own work
❌ Misleading others about authorship

### Security Notice
This portfolio demonstrates security best practices and patterns, including:
- OWASP Top 10 protections
- JWT authentication
- Content Security Policy (CSP)
- Secure API design
- Encryption and data protection

Users are responsible for:
- Reviewing and understanding security implementations
- Conducting security audits of their own deployments
- Implementing environment-specific security measures
- Following PCI-DSS and data protection regulations if handling payment data

### No Warranty
This software is provided as a portfolio/reference implementation.
The author makes no warranties regarding suitability for production,
security of deployments, or compliance with any regulations.

